Bilinear Algorithm¶

Row expanded step¶

In [0]:
row_expanded = np.zeros((img.shape[0],(img.shape[1]*2)-1))
In [0]:
for i in range (0,row_expanded.shape[0]):
      for j in range (0,row_expanded.shape[1]):
        if ( j % 2 == 0 ):
            row_expanded[i][j]= img[i][int(j/2)]
        else :
              row_expanded[i][j] = img[i][j//2]//2 +  img[i][(j//2)+1]//2
    
plt.imshow(row_expanded,cmap="gray")
Out[0]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x7fed30188c50>

Columns expanded step¶

In [0]:
zoomed = np.zeros(((row_expanded.shape[0]*2)-1,row_expanded.shape[1]))
In [0]:
for i in range (0,zoomed.shape[0]):
    for j in range (0,zoomed.shape[1]):
        if ( i % 2 == 0 ):
              zoomed[i][j]= row_expanded[i//2][j]
        else :
              zoomed[i][j] = (row_expanded[i//2][j] +  row_expanded[(i//2)+1][j])//2
